uired before calculations | [DATA ROBUSTNESS RULE] Handle missing, malformed, or inconsistent data safely | [BOOLEAN HANDLING RULE] Normalize boolean values before comparison | [DATA CONSISTENCY RULE] Respect dataset schema | [SUPPORT FILES RULE] If env/config is used, include: 1. Instructional sentence 2. File content in markdown code block 3. BEFORE the main code | [DIFFICULTY RULE] Complexity MUST match level | [EXPLANATION RULE] Explanation within 'Mini-Lección' MUST explain WHAT, WHY, HOW, and real-world context concisely | [LEARNING RULE] Each example MUST highlight a key insight | [COMMON MISTAKES RULE] Include a short mistake note after each example | [MINI CHALLENGE RULE] Include a short reinforcement question after each example | [REAL WORLD RULE] Connect each example to a real-world use case | [FORMAT RULE] Only valid markdown code blocks allowed | [LANGUAGE TAG RULE] ALWAYS label markdown code blocks with the correct underlying programming language (e.g., python, javascript, sql) | [OUTPUT FORMAT RULE] Monetary values formatted with '$', commas, 2 decimals using f-strings. | [CONSISTENCY RULE] All examples MUST have similar complexity and length | [FINAL OUTPUT RULE] Include Key Takeaway section at the end | [HEADER RULE - STRICT] You MUST start your entire response EXACTLY with this markdown block (do not print anything before it):
